{"kind":"concept","id":10,"concept_type":"Contract","name":"C-2025-003","description":"Software Licensing Agreement — Contract C-2025-003\r\n\r\nEffective date: July 1, 2025\r\nTerm: 12 months.\r\n\r\nParties:\r\n  - Acme Labs (the \"Licensor\"), Lyon, France.\r\n  - Initech (the \"Licensee\"), Austin, Texas, USA.\r\n\r\nScope:\r\n  Acme Labs grants Initech a non-exclusive, non-transferable annual\r\n  licence to deploy Acme's industrial automation control software (\"Tier\r\n  A\" edition) on up to fifty Initech-owned production lines. The licence\r\n  bundles premium support: 24/7 incident response, two scheduled review\r\n  meetings per quarter, and prioritized hotfix delivery.\r\n\r\nCommercial terms:\r\n  Total contract value: 80,000 EUR for the year. Billed in two parts:\r\n  45,000 EUR upfront for the licence and 35,000 EUR for premium support\r\n  in September. Net 30 payment terms.\r\n\r\nSignatories:\r\n  Alice Martin, CTO — Acme Labs\r\n  Carol Diaz, Head of Procurement — Initech\r\n","properties":{}}
